'''Sir Frank P. Lowy''', {{post-nominals|country=AUS|size=100%|AC}} (born 22 October 1930) is a [[Czechoslovak]]-born [[Australian people|Australian]]-[[Israeli people|Israeli]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Pilger|first=John|title=War and shopping – the extremism that never speaks its name|work=New Statesman (1996)|date=September 26, 2011|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2469505591.html|quote=The co-founder of Westfield is Frank Lowy, an Australian -Israeli billionaire who is to shopping what Rupert Murdoch is to media.|publisher=via HighBeam {{Subscription required}} }}</ref><ref name="cashman">{{cite web|last=Cashman|first=Greer Fay|title=The Australian connection|work=Jerusalem Post|date=August 8, 2012|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-207930892.html|quote=Among the many Australian citizens who have homes in Israel as well as business interests in this country is billionaire Frank Lowy, one of the wealthiest people in Australia, who is often described in the media as an Australian-Israeli businessman even though he was born in Czechoslovakia.|publisher=via HighBeam {{Subscription required}} }}</ref> businessman and the former long-time Chairman of [[Westfield Corporation]], a global shopping centre company with US$29.3&nbsp;billion of assets under management in the United States, United Kingdom and Europe. In June 2018 Westfield Corporation was acquired by French company Unibail-Rodamco<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.afr.com/brand/chanticleer/how-westfields-frank-lowy-consummated-australias-biggest-ma-deal-20180315-h0xj21|title=How Westfield's Frank Lowy consummated Australia's biggest M&A deal|date=2018-03-15|work=Financial Review|access-date=2018-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref>. He is a former Chairman of [[Scentre Group]], the owner and manager of [[Westfield Group|Westfield]]-branded shopping centres in Australia and New Zealand.<ref>http://www.scentregroup.com/about/board/</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/business/property/frank-lowy-to-retire-as-chairman-of-scentre-group-20151023-gkgrdb.html |title=Frank Lowy to retire as chairman of Scentre Group |author=Danckert, Sarah |work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=23 October 2015 |accessdate=7 June 2016 }}</ref>

With an assessed [[net worth]] of {{AUD}}8.26&nbsp;[[1,000,000,000 (number)|billion]] in 2017, Lowy is ranked as the fourth richest Australian according to the ''[[Financial Review Rich List]]'';<ref name="afr2017"/> having been the richest person in Australia during 2010.<ref name=smh2010>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/executive-style/luxury/frank-lowy-tops-brw-rich-list-for-first-time-20100526-wd2n.html |title=Frank Lowy tops BRW rich list for first time |author=Zappone, Chris |date=26 May 2010 |accessdate=27 July 2011 |work=The Sydney Morning Herald }}</ref><ref name=smh2010a>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/executive-style/luxury/lowy-leaves-mining-magnates-in-the-dust-20100526-we91.html |title=Lowy leaves mining magnates in the dust |author1=Saulwick, Jacob |author2=Cummins, Caroline |date=27 May 2010 |accessdate=27 July 2011 |work=The Sydney Morning Herald }}</ref> ''[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes Asia]]'' magazine assessed Lowy's net worth at {{USD}}4.6&nbsp;billion in January 2014.<ref name="Forbes2014"/>

==Biography==

===Early life===
Lowy was born in [[Czechoslovakia]]<ref name="cashman"/> (in what is now [[Slovakia]]), and was forced to live in a ghetto in [[Hungary]] during World War II.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hewett|first=Jennifer|title=Holocaust truth set Frank Lowy free|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/archive/business-old/holocaust-truth-set-frank-lowy-free/story-e6frg9gx-1225952919237?nk=728c50eb35798482b4f4d13453775a3f-1467928777|publisher=The Australian|date=November 13, 2010}}</ref> He made his way to France in 1946, where he boarded the ship ''Yagur'', heading for [[Mandatory Palestine]]. However, he was caught en route by the British authorities and interned in a [[Cyprus internment camps|detention camp in Cyprus]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Keinon|first=Herb|title=Frank Lowy: From Hagana to $3.8 billion magnate|work=Jerusalem Post|date=May 30, 2006|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-124649874.html|quote=One of 750 passengers who after World War II left France on board the illegal immigrant ship Yagur, Lowy was caught en route by the British and deported to the detention camp in Cyprus.|publisher=via HighBeam {{Subscription required}} }}</ref> Lowy joined the [[Haganah]], and then the [[Golani Brigade]], and fought in the [[1948 Arab–Israeli War]] in the [[Galilee]] and [[Gaza Strip|Gaza]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Keinon|first=Herb|title=Frank Lowy: From Hagana to $3.8 billion magnate|work=Jerusalem Post|date=May 30, 2006|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-124649874.html|quote=From Atlit Lowy eventually joined the Hagana and then the Golani Brigade, fighting during the War of Independence in the Galilee and in Gaza.|publisher=via HighBeam {{Subscription required}} }}</ref>

===Career===
In 1952, Lowy left [[Israel]] and joined his family, who had left Europe for Australia and started a business delivering small goods.<ref name="age2004"/> In 1953, he met fellow immigrant John Saunders.<ref>{{ cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/business/cbd/singin-in-the-rain-in-the-hunter-valley-20160509-gopnnj.html#ixzz4AuhOaCJ9 |title=CBD: Frank's back|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |author=Kruger, Colin |date=10 May 2016 |access-date=7 June 2016 }}</ref> The pair became business partners, eventually creating Westfield Development Corporation through the development of a shopping centre at [[Blacktown, New South Wales|Blacktown]] in [[Greater Western Sydney|Sydney's western suburbs]].<ref name="age2004">{{cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/04/23/1082616328856.html |title=No longer a family affair|work=[[The Age]] |author1=Myer, Rod |author2=Lynch, Michael |date=24 April 2004 |accessdate=7 June 2016 }}</ref> Over the next 30 years, Lowy and Saunders developed shopping centres across Australia and the United States (from 1977);<ref name="age2004"/> and listed the company on the [[Australian Stock Exchange]] in 1960 as Westfield Development Corporation.<ref name="age2004"/> Saunders sold his interests and left the company in 1987.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} In the 1990s Lowy took the company to New Zealand, then the United Kingdom in the 2000s.<ref name="age2004"/>

Lowy was appointed a Director of the [[Reserve Bank of Australia]] in 1995, and was reappointed in 2000 and 2003, concluding his term in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rba.gov.au/about-rba/history/rba-board-members.html |title=Past & Present Reserve Bank Board Members |publisher=Reserve Bank of Australia |work=About the RBA |year=2011 |accessdate=30 July 2011  }}</ref> In 2008 Lowy and related interests were mentioned in documents stolen from the [[LGT Bank]] of [[Liechtenstein]] by a former employee. A subsequent US Senate probe and an [[Australian Taxation Office]] audit in which Lowy and his sons, David and Steven, were investigated on their involvement with financial institutions in [[tax haven]]s located in [[Liechtenstein]] and [[Switzerland]]. Lowy maintained he had not done anything wrong and the matter was settled with the ATO and no action was taken after that.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.afr.com/news/death-and-taxes-how-frank-lowy-faced-off-one-and-settled-the-other-20150717-gienni?login_token=vn4hSSCXXwclO_mpYqN7EJgEk2yPLN6VFgzzbmQHqB0z-_qC0ORPLtbnMzwqvr6cCKMgQjHB1SfbFxBoP_MpNQ&expiry=1461121046&single_use_token=AFFYm4n3ORE4hjw8SdzqfCbQg77fS_A7xv_jI4jzoE8QTHu4s4nZVOQAKA2cKuK20uZzNHSL0JlSqcFvhMXAkQ|work=The Australian Financial Review|accessdate=20 April 2016|date=18 July 2015|title=Death and taxes: how Frank Lowy faced off one and settled the other}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/world/probe-into-lowys-offshore-banking/2008/07/17/1216163002718.html|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|accessdate=17 July 2008|date=17 July 2008|title=Probe into Lowys offshore banking}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/business/us-ran-two-investigations-into-lowys-bank-links-20101208-18pxy.html |work=The Age |location=Australia |title=US ran two investigations into Lowys' bank links |author=Wood, Leonie |date=9 December 2010 |accessdate=29 July 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author1=Elliott, Geoff |author2=Hewett, Jennifer |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/lowy-family-hid-millions/story-e6frg6tf-1111116947059 |work=The Australian |date=18 July 2008 |accessdate=29 July 2011 |title=Lowy family 'hid millions' }}</ref>

After turning 80 in October 2010, effective May 2011, Lowy officially stood down as Executive Chairman of the Westfield Group, taking on the role of Non-Executive Chairman. Sons, [[Steven Lowy|Steven]] and Peter, became joint chief executives.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/lowy-hands-westfield-reins-to-sons/story-e6frg6nf-1226014964138 |title=Frank Lowy hands Westfield reins to sons |author=Hewett, Jennifer |date=3 March 2011 |work=The Australian |accessdate=30 July 2011 }}</ref>

In October 2015, Lowy stepped down as the chairman of the [[Scentre Group]], a role that he had held for 55 years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Frank Lowy steps down as Scentre Group chairman |url=http://www.afr.com/real-estate/frank-lowy-steps-down-as-chair-of-scentre-group-20151023-gkgrpo|work=[[Financial Review]] |location=Australia |date=23 October 2015}}</ref>

==Personal life==
[[File:Frank Lowy.jpg|thumb|Lowy at the 2013 March of the Living in Auschwitz-Birkenau in front of the cattle car donated in memory of his father, Hugo.]]
Lowy is married to Shirley, whom he met at a Jewish dance when he was 21. He has three sons, Peter and Steven, who manage the Westfield business, and David, who manages the family's private investments.<ref name=Oz2010-11-03>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/business-old/property/holocaust-truth-set-frank-lowy-free/story-e6frg9gx-1225952919237 |title=Holocaust truth set Frank Lowy free |author=Hewett, Jennifer |work=The Australian |date=3 November 2010 |accessdate=30 July 2011 }}</ref> His wife is founder of the Chai Foundation which is dedicated to finding and funding research into effective but less toxic forms of cancer therapy.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://jewishcarensw.blogspot.com/2011/06/chai-and-jewishcare-working-together-to.html |publisher=Jewish Care NSW |title=Chai Foundation and JewishCare sign historical agreement |date=29 June 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304220721/http://jewishcarensw.blogspot.com/2011/06/chai-and-jewishcare-working-together-to.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> His son Peter, is chairman of Tribe Media Corp, the parent of the [[The Jewish Journal of Greater Los Angeles|Jewish Journal]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.jewishjournal.com/los_angeles/article/seeking_impact_funders_convene_in_l.a |work=Jewish Journal |title=Seeking impact, Jewish funders convene in L.A. |first=Jonah |last=Lowenfeld |date=March 19, 2013 }}</ref> and served as chairman of the [[University of Judaism]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.jewishjournal.com/opinion/article/a_big_giver_20070323/ |work=Jewish Journal |title=A Big Giver |first=Rob |last=Eshman |date=March 22, 2007 }}</ref>

In an [[ABC1|Australian television production]] broadcast in 2010, called ''Family Confidential'', it was revealed that Lowy had kept a secret about his survival in Nazi occupied Hungary.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} As a 13-year-old Jewish boy, Lowy had never known about the loss of his father, Hugo Lowy, who was beaten to death at [[Auschwitz concentration camp]] for refusing to leave his Jewish prayer shawl (Talit and Tefilin) behind<ref name=Oz2010-11-03/>. As a mark of respect to Hugo Lowy and other Hungarian Jews, Lowy commissioned the restoration of a railway wagon that had transported Hungarian Jews to Auschwitz, and placed the wagon on site at the former concentration camp.<ref name=Oz2010-11-03/> In April 2013, Frank Lowy attended the ''[[March of the Living]]'', where he shared the story of how his father, Hugo Lowy, perished during the Holocaust, with thousands of young students from around the world who had gathered in [[Auschwitz-Birkenau]] to observe Holocaust Remembrance Day ([[Yom HaShoah]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jta.org/2013/04/10/news-opinion/world/frank-lowy-recalls-fathers-demise-in-march-of-the-living-address#ixzz2uZkMPVw7 |title=Frank Lowy recalls father's demise in March of the Living address|accessdate=10 April 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yadvashem.org/yv/en/education/international_projects/the_wagon/index.asp  |title= The Wagon of Birkenau|accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref>

===Wealth===
Lowy has appeared on the ''[[Financial Review Rich List]]'', formerly the ''BRW Rich 200'' list, every year since it was first published in 1983.<ref name="afr2017"/><ref name="BRW2013-Thomson">{{cite journal|url=http://www.brw.com.au/p/lists/rich-200/2013/celebrating_years_of_the_rich_EnUWZtuD02H4jYBFx0e3MM|last=Thomson|first=James|date=22 May 2013|accessdate=22 May 2013|title=Celebrating 30 years of the Rich 200|work=BRW Rich 200}}</ref> In 2010, the ''BRW'' magazine measured Lowy's wealth at {{AUD}}5.04&nbsp;billion, making him Australia's richest person at that time.<ref name=smh2010/><ref name=smh2010a/> In 2014, his net wealth was assessed at {{AUD}}7.16&nbsp;billion by the ''BRW'' magazine and {{USD}}4.60&nbsp;billion by the ''Forbes'' magazine.<ref name="Forbes2014"/><ref name="brw2014"/> In 2016 his wealth was assesed as {{AUD}}8.26&nbsp;billion on the ''BRW Rich 200'' list;<ref name="BRW 2016">{{cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-05-26/brw-rich-list-topped-by-harry-triguboff/7448044 |title=BRW rich list topped by Harry Triguboff, Gina Rinehart slips to fourth |work=ABC News |access-date=26 May 2016 |date=26 May 2016}}</ref> and the same net worth the following year when the list was renamed as the ''Financial Review Rich List.''<ref name="afr2017"/>

