Sheikh '''Mansour bin Hamdan bin Hamid al-Wayeou' al-Aradi al-Balawi'''  ({{lang-ar|منصور بن حمدان بن حامد الوعيوع العرادي البلوي}}) (born 1964, [[Jeddah]]) was the Chairman of [[Saudi Arabia]]n sport club [[Al-Ittihad (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] from 2003 to 2008, in a famous boom period where he contributed to the club's major domestic and international achievements.<ref>{{cite news |title=Saudi bid for Keane falls through |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/4486034.stm |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=30 November 2005 |accessdate=18 February 2011 }}</ref> He is considered to be one of the richest people in Saudi Arabia, and has a variety of diverse companies and real estates which he inherited from his father.

